cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL

This paper is about analyzing the effect of a diversity-inducing regularization method on the generalization performance of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses neural networks for the empirical study, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
